1. d4 (1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6) 1... Nf6 2. Bf4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 { [%csl Gd6] } (4... O-O?! { This move is clearly
dubious, but a lot of players will not pay attention to the importance of move
order and play this } 5. e5! Ne8 (5... Nh5?! 6. Bd2! { Threatening to trap
the knight with g4 } 6... f5 7. h3 Bh8 (7... f4 8. Nf3 d6 9. Bc4+ Kh8 10. Qe2) 8. Be2 Ng7 9. h4) 6. Nf3 d6 7. Bc4 dxe5 8. dxe5 Qxd1+ 9. Rxd1 Bg4 10. Rd8) (4... d5 5. e5 (5. Nb5!?) 5... Ne4 6. Nce2) 5. Qd2 O-O (5... Nh5?! { Just leads to more
issues for black } 6. Bh6! $16) (5... Nbd7 6. O-O-O c5 7. dxc5 Nxc5 8. e5 Nfe4 9. Nxe4 Nxe4 10. Qe1! $18 { An improvement from Eric Rosen vs Andrea/
Alexandra Botez 2020 }) (5... h5 { Alexandra's weird move of choice } 6. Nf3 Nbd7 7. e5! { Black is now in trouble... } 7... dxe5 (7... Ng4 8. e6!) 8. dxe5 Ng4 9. O-O-O { The engine alreeady evalutes this as +6 for white! } 9... c6 10. Bc4 Qa5 11. Bxf7+ Kxf7 12. e6+ Kxe6 13. Ng5+ Kf6 14. Nce4+ Kf5 15. Qxa5+) 6. O-O-O c6 (6... c5? 7. dxc5 Qa5 8. cxd6 $18) (6... Nbd7 7. Bh6 c5 8. Bxg7 Kxg7 9. e5! Ne8 10. exd6 Nxd6 11. dxc5 Nxc5 12. Qd4+ $18) 7. Bh6 b5 8. f3 a5 (8... b4 9. Nce2 Qa5 10. Kb1 Be6 11. Nc1 Nbd7 12. h4 Nb6 13. h5 Nxh5 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. g4 Nf6 16. Qh6+ Kg8 17. d5 cxd5 18. Nb3 Qa4 19. g5 Nh5 20. Rxh5 gxh5 21. Bd3 $18) 9. Kb1 b4 10. Nce2 a4 11. h4 b3 12. cxb3 axb3 13. a3 Qa5 14. Nc3 Nh5 15. Nge2 Bxh6 16. Qxh6 Ba6 17. g4 Bxe2 18. Nxe2 Ng7 19. h5 g5 20. Nc3 Nd7 21. e5 f6 22. Bd3 f5 23. Qxg5 Kh8 24. h6 Ne6 25. Qxe7 $18 { Rosen - Corrales US Open Blitz 2019 } *


